WEBVTT

00:01.543 --> 00:02.669
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: Are you ready?</i>

00:02.752 --> 00:04.170
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

00:04.254 --> 00:07.257
{\an8}<i>♪ I know you see me</i>
<i>standing here ♪</i>

00:08.216 --> 00:11.428
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good,</i>
<i>my dear? ♪</i>

00:12.220 --> 00:14.597
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good today? ♪</i>

00:14.681 --> 00:17.559
{\an8}<i>♪ Today, today ♪</i>

00:17.642 --> 00:19.728
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

00:20.812 --> 00:23.189
{\an8}<i>♪ I'm just another</i>
<i>kind of girl ♪</i>

00:25.233 --> 00:28.778
{\an8}<i>♪ And you want</i>
<i>to see my world ♪</i>

00:28.862 --> 00:31.698
{\an8}<i>♪ So come and run away ♪</i>

00:31.781 --> 00:33.825
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:33.908 --> 00:35.994
{\an8}<i>♪ If you wanna play ♪</i>

00:36.077 --> 00:38.037
{\an8}<i>♪ Come and play today ♪</i>

00:38.121 --> 00:42.000
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's just get away, yeah ♪</i>

00:42.083 --> 00:44.711
{\an8}<i>♪ I will make you see ♪</i>

00:44.794 --> 00:45.670
{\an8}<i>♪ All of the things ♪</i>

00:45.754 --> 00:47.797
{\an8}<i>♪ That you can be ♪</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:49.799
{\an8}<i>♪ Believe in yourself ♪</i>

00:49.883 --> 00:53.636
{\an8}<i>♪ Come follow me ♪</i>

00:53.720 --> 00:56.139
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:56.222 --> 00:57.432
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

01:03.730 --> 01:07.901
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:07.984 --> 01:09.819
- I can't believe
I have two tests tomorrow.

01:09.903 --> 01:11.946
- Well, I have to turn in
a 10-page paper

01:12.030 --> 01:13.615
and I haven't even started yet.

01:13.698 --> 01:15.366
- Yeah?
Well, I have more homework

01:15.450 --> 01:18.203
than both of you guys
put together.

01:18.286 --> 01:20.580
- Hey, pass the suntan lotion,
would ya?

01:20.663 --> 01:21.664
- Sure.

01:21.748 --> 01:25.418
{\an8}<i>[pop music playing on radio]</i>

01:25.502 --> 01:27.837
{\an8}You know,
we really should be studying.

01:27.921 --> 01:29.047
- Yeah, we should.

01:29.130 --> 01:30.298
- So should.

01:30.381 --> 01:31.382
- But we're just gonna
stay here

01:31.466 --> 01:32.425
and lay in the sun, right?

01:32.509 --> 01:33.426
- Oh, yeah.

01:33.510 --> 01:34.427
- Absolutely.

01:34.511 --> 01:36.221
- Oh, thank God.

01:36.304 --> 01:37.889
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:37.972 --> 01:40.016
{\an8}- Hey.
What are you people

01:40.099 --> 01:41.351
{\an8}doing up on our roof?

01:41.434 --> 01:42.894
What are they doing
up on our roof?

01:42.977 --> 01:44.854
- They appear to be
lying on chairs.

01:44.938 --> 01:45.939
- Our chairs.

01:46.022 --> 01:47.315
- Why are you all cranky?

01:47.398 --> 01:48.983
- Someone hide your mirror?

01:49.067 --> 01:49.984
[laughter]

01:50.068 --> 01:50.401
- Funny.
Now get off our roof.

01:50.485 --> 01:52.403
- No.

01:52.487 --> 01:53.696
- We're not bothering you.

01:53.780 --> 01:55.073
- Why should we have to leave?

01:55.156 --> 01:56.741
{\an8}- Because this is
the guys' dorm,

01:56.825 --> 01:59.828
{\an8}which means this roof is
for guys only.

01:59.911 --> 02:01.162
- Chase, tell Logan
he's being an idiot.

02:01.246 --> 02:05.458
- Actually,
I kind of agree with him.

02:05.542 --> 02:06.543
- Thank you.
- Huh?

02:06.626 --> 02:07.919
- Chase!

02:08.002 --> 02:08.544
- You're taking Logan's side
on this?

02:08.627 --> 02:11.297
- Well, look,

02:11.381 --> 02:11.840
PCA was just a guy school

02:11.923 --> 02:14.425
for a long time.

02:14.509 --> 02:17.053
Then they let girls in,
which is great.

02:17.137 --> 02:18.221
- Sometimes.

02:18.304 --> 02:20.056
- But I think the guys do
kind of

02:20.139 --> 02:23.434
need a place where we can just,
you know, be guys.

02:23.518 --> 02:25.061
- Fine.
So pull up a chair and burp.

02:25.144 --> 02:26.312
We don't care.

02:26.396 --> 02:27.730
- Guys can't just be guys

02:27.814 --> 02:29.065
when there's girls around.

02:29.149 --> 02:30.358
- Why not?

02:30.441 --> 02:31.943
- 'Cause when females
hang around males,

02:32.026 --> 02:34.445
it just causes the males
to behave differently.

02:34.529 --> 02:35.738
They can't help it.

02:35.822 --> 02:37.407
- It's basic biology.

02:37.490 --> 02:39.784
- You got a C-minus in biology.

02:39.868 --> 02:41.452
- Yeah?
But who was the best-looking

02:41.536 --> 02:42.787
guy in the class, huh?

02:42.871 --> 02:44.664
Yeah, me.

02:44.747 --> 02:46.416
- Uh...
[clears throat]

02:46.499 --> 02:47.167
I was in that class.

02:47.250 --> 02:48.209
- What's your point?

02:48.293 --> 02:49.794
- Okay, I admit,
guys do act different

02:49.878 --> 02:51.421
when girls are around,

02:51.504 --> 02:53.339
but it's not 'cause of
"nature" or biology.

02:53.423 --> 02:56.718
- Right, it's 'cause of
dumbness and stupidity.

02:56.801 --> 02:57.594
- There you go.

02:57.677 --> 02:59.345
Now why don't you be nice boys

02:59.429 --> 03:00.597
and go fix us
some more lemonade?

03:00.680 --> 03:03.016
- Uh-uh.
Now leave.

03:03.099 --> 03:04.100
- No.

03:04.183 --> 03:05.268
- Uh-oh.
She crossed her arms.

03:05.351 --> 03:07.270
- It's on.
- So on.

03:07.353 --> 03:08.813
- Fine.
Then I'll just go

03:08.897 --> 03:11.065
tell our dorm advisor
to make you leave our roof.

03:11.149 --> 03:12.317
- Then I'll talk to him too.

03:12.400 --> 03:14.068
- Me too.

03:14.152 --> 03:17.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:17.989 --> 03:20.325
- Uh, hey,
can you turn up the music?

03:20.408 --> 03:22.160
- Yeah, sure.

03:22.243 --> 03:24.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:24.203 --> 03:25.079
Hey, cool boom box.

03:25.163 --> 03:28.291
- Oh, thanks.
I just got it.

03:28.374 --> 03:30.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:30.418 --> 03:32.170
[electricity crackles]

03:35.673 --> 03:38.301
- Was it expensive?

03:38.384 --> 03:41.471
[all talking at once]

03:44.307 --> 03:47.060
- Hey! Hey!
All right, cool it.

03:47.143 --> 03:49.145
So why can't you girls lay out
on your own roof?

03:49.228 --> 03:50.396
- 'Cause our roof's lame.

03:50.480 --> 03:51.856
- Yeah.
It doesn't get any sun

03:51.940 --> 03:53.232
and it has bugs
and there's a tree above it

03:53.316 --> 03:55.401
with a bunch of squirrels
so it smells like squirrel pee.

03:55.485 --> 03:57.528
- Look, PCA used to be
just for guys only,

03:57.612 --> 03:59.572
and now our roof is
the last place we've got

03:59.656 --> 04:00.823
that's just for us.

04:00.907 --> 04:02.158
- Girls, listen.
The roof is part of

04:02.241 --> 04:04.327
the boys' dorm, so if they
want to keep it private,

04:04.410 --> 04:05.161
I think they have a right to.

04:05.244 --> 04:07.455
- Ha!
Later, losers.

04:07.538 --> 04:09.332
[both scoff]

04:09.415 --> 04:11.376
- Okay,
if we can't go on their roof,

04:11.459 --> 04:13.419
then they can't come in
the girls' lounge anymore.

04:13.503 --> 04:14.921
- Uh, yes, they can.

04:15.004 --> 04:15.880
- Nicole.

04:15.964 --> 04:16.673
- Conversation over.

04:16.755 --> 04:18.048
You're free to go now.

04:20.760 --> 04:21.844
- Why did you do that?

04:21.928 --> 04:23.179
- 'Cause I like
guys hanging out

04:23.262 --> 04:24.180
in the girls' lounge.

04:24.263 --> 04:25.181
That lounge is my ice cream,

04:25.264 --> 04:26.891
and boys are the sprinkles.

04:26.975 --> 04:29.352
- Whatever.
I gotta go see Dustin.

04:29.435 --> 04:30.979
- Okay, I'll come with you.

04:31.062 --> 04:33.189
- He's in the infirmary
with chickenpox.

04:33.272 --> 04:35.024
- Bye.
Have fun.

04:35.108 --> 04:38.027
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

04:38.111 --> 04:46.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:47.370 --> 04:49.247
- Knock knock.

04:49.330 --> 04:50.790
- Oh, hey, Zoe.

04:50.873 --> 04:52.250
- So I talked to
your roommate's mom.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.043
Turns out he's already had
the chickenpox.

04:54.127 --> 04:57.296
So you don't have to stay here
in the infirmary anymore.

04:57.380 --> 04:58.715
- Um, thanks,

04:58.798 --> 05:00.717
but I think I should stay
a couple more nights.

05:00.800 --> 05:02.218
- But if you feel okay,
why would you want

05:02.301 --> 05:04.262
to stay in the infirmary?

05:04.345 --> 05:05.680
- I don't know.
I just...

05:05.763 --> 05:07.306
- Hey, Dustin.

05:07.390 --> 05:09.934
- Hey, Shannon.

05:10.018 --> 05:10.768
- Shannon?

05:10.852 --> 05:13.104
- [whispers]
My nurse.

05:13.187 --> 05:15.857
Shannon, this is my sister Zoey.

05:15.940 --> 05:17.275
- Hi.

05:17.358 --> 05:18.901
Thought you might like
a little ice cream.

05:18.985 --> 05:21.362
- You thought right...again.

05:21.446 --> 05:22.780
- Oh, Dustin.

05:22.864 --> 05:23.990
- Well,
I'll leave you two alone.

05:24.073 --> 05:25.283
- Wait.
Before you go,

05:25.366 --> 05:28.536
can you take a picture
of me and Shannon

05:28.619 --> 05:29.912
with your phone?

05:29.996 --> 05:30.997
- Sure.

05:32.540 --> 05:35.793
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:35.877 --> 05:37.170
Say "pox."

05:37.253 --> 05:38.296
both: Pox!

05:38.379 --> 05:39.756
[phone beeps]

05:39.839 --> 05:41.257
- Okay, I'll check on you
in a few minutes.

05:41.340 --> 05:42.508
Nice to meet you, Zoey.

05:42.592 --> 05:43.634
- Yeah, you too.

05:45.011 --> 05:47.180
So who do you want me to
send this picture to?

05:47.263 --> 05:48.723
- Everyone.

05:48.806 --> 05:49.766
<i>MAN: ♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

05:49.849 --> 05:53.770
<i>[lively music]</i>

05:53.853 --> 05:58.316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:58.399 --> 06:02.612
- I hate our roof.
I hate it so much.

06:02.695 --> 06:04.072
- It gets, like, no sun.

06:04.155 --> 06:06.949
- Yeah, I think I'm actually
getting whiter.

06:07.033 --> 06:09.202
- And it smells like
squirrel pee.

06:09.285 --> 06:11.204
- See?
I'm not crazy.

06:11.287 --> 06:12.622
- Hey, you know what?

06:12.705 --> 06:13.956
- What?
- Hmm?

06:14.040 --> 06:15.375
- Maybe we ought to prove
to Chase and Logan

06:15.458 --> 06:18.920
that guys can be "just guys"
even when girls are around.

06:19.003 --> 06:20.296
- How are we gonna do that?

06:20.379 --> 06:21.631
- By being around them

06:21.714 --> 06:23.132
when they don't know
we're around.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.967
- But if we're around
trying to prove it,

06:25.051 --> 06:26.844
we'll be around them,
and we're girls.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.846
So they'll be around girls
when we're trying to--

06:28.930 --> 06:30.598
- Maybe you should
let Zoey talk.

06:30.681 --> 06:31.307
- I'm saying,
what if one of us

06:31.390 --> 06:33.851
pretends to be a guy?

06:33.935 --> 06:35.436
- Okay,
four problems with that:

06:35.520 --> 06:36.896
hair, face, boobs.

06:36.979 --> 06:38.314
- That's three problems.

06:38.397 --> 06:39.816
- Two boobs.

06:39.899 --> 06:42.193
- We can get around
those problems.

06:42.276 --> 06:44.570
- It would be
the ultimate acting challenge,

06:44.654 --> 06:46.364
and I am the ultimate actress.

06:46.447 --> 06:48.074
- You really think
you can convince

06:48.157 --> 06:49.367
Chase and Logan
that you're a guy?

06:49.450 --> 06:51.828
- Easy. Chase is gullible
and Logan's a moron.

06:51.911 --> 06:53.788
- Okay, but if
we're gonna do this right,

06:53.871 --> 06:55.957
then we're gonna need
a little inside help.

06:57.458 --> 06:58.668
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:58.751 --> 07:00.461
Lola's gonna pretend
to be a guy?

07:00.545 --> 07:02.004
- Yeah.

07:02.088 --> 07:03.923
- Uh, okay, I can think of
three problems with that.

07:04.006 --> 07:05.174
- Don't worry about those.

07:05.258 --> 07:06.884
Will you help us?

07:06.968 --> 07:10.555
- Uh...make a fool out of
my roommates?

07:10.638 --> 07:11.347
Sure, what'cha want me to do?

07:11.430 --> 07:13.683
- Okay, first, you help us turn

07:13.766 --> 07:15.476
Lola into a believable guy.

07:15.560 --> 07:18.229
You'll be sort of like
our guy consultant.

07:18.312 --> 07:19.730
- Okay.

07:19.814 --> 07:22.358
- And you can't stay in
your room for a couple of days.

07:22.441 --> 07:23.609
- Why not?

07:23.693 --> 07:24.694
- 'Cause we're gonna make Lola

07:24.777 --> 07:26.195
the new temporary roommate.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.197
- And where am I
supposed to sleep?

07:28.281 --> 07:29.240
- You pretend to be sick

07:29.323 --> 07:30.908
and you can sleep
in the infirmary.

07:30.992 --> 07:32.201
- Oh, no.
Uh-uh.

07:32.285 --> 07:34.328
No, I heard about
Nurse Crutcher. Mm-mmm.

07:34.412 --> 07:36.747
- No, they have a new nurse.

07:36.831 --> 07:38.124
Want to see her?

07:38.207 --> 07:39.208
- Okay.

07:39.292 --> 07:40.251
[phone beeps]

07:40.334 --> 07:41.419
- Well?

07:41.502 --> 07:43.045
- Well, I think

07:43.129 --> 07:45.006
I'm coming down with a fever.

07:45.089 --> 07:46.549
Ugh!

07:46.632 --> 07:49.552
<i>[lively music]</i>

07:49.635 --> 07:52.680
[laughter]

07:55.850 --> 07:56.851
- Okay, Lola.

07:56.934 --> 07:58.853
- You ready to become a guy?

07:58.936 --> 08:01.689
- Yup.
Make me a dude.

08:01.772 --> 08:03.065
[laughs]

08:03.149 --> 08:03.941
<i>[pop music]</i>

08:04.025 --> 08:05.443
<i>MAN: ♪ You think you can tell ♪</i>

08:05.526 --> 08:07.195
<i>♪ You think that you know ♪</i>

08:07.278 --> 08:10.781
<i>♪ You think that it's true</i>
<i>if you say so ♪</i>

08:10.865 --> 08:11.574
<i>♪ But figure it out ♪</i>

08:11.657 --> 08:13.743
<i>♪ It's only a game ♪</i>

08:13.826 --> 08:15.203
<i>♪ You're seeing</i>
<i>the same old face ♪</i>

08:15.286 --> 08:19.332
<i>♪ And time with a new name ♪</i>

08:19.415 --> 08:27.423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:34.514 --> 08:37.767
<i>♪ Maybe you think</i>
<i>I'm wasting my time ♪</i>

08:37.850 --> 08:40.937
<i>♪ Standing around</i>
<i>in the wrong line ♪</i>

08:41.020 --> 08:42.438
<i>♪ But look in my eyes ♪</i>

08:42.520 --> 08:43.688
<i>♪ I need you to see ♪</i>

08:43.773 --> 08:46.108
<i>♪ Think that</i>
<i>I just might change your mind ♪</i>

08:46.192 --> 08:49.278
<i>♪ If you let me ♪</i>

08:49.362 --> 08:55.284
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:55.368 --> 08:58.913
<i>♪ And how could you tell</i>
<i>if I was to change ♪</i>

08:58.996 --> 09:01.916
<i>♪ Into the same thing ♪</i>

09:01.999 --> 09:03.501
<i>♪ And how would you know ♪</i>

09:03.584 --> 09:06.128
<i>♪ When they always told you ♪</i>

09:06.212 --> 09:11.133
<i>♪ What to be? ♪</i>

09:11.217 --> 09:17.181
<i>♪ Ahh, ahh, ahh ♪</i>

09:17.265 --> 09:21.060
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:21.143 --> 09:22.853
[clapping]

09:22.937 --> 09:23.813
ZOEY: Whoo!

09:23.896 --> 09:26.107
- Well?

09:26.190 --> 09:26.857
- Unbelievable.

09:26.941 --> 09:27.817
- I could almost date you.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.777
- Come here, baby.
[smooching]

09:29.860 --> 09:32.321
- No, no, no, no, no.
Back off, boy.

09:32.405 --> 09:34.657
- [laughs]
Michael, what'cha think?

09:34.740 --> 09:38.577
- It's good, but I still vote
for the mustache.

09:38.661 --> 09:39.787
- Yeah.
Well, it's time for you

09:39.870 --> 09:41.497
to stop voting and go check into

09:41.580 --> 09:41.872
the infirmary, okay?

09:41.956 --> 09:43.958
- Okay.

09:44.041 --> 09:45.209
But don't you think

09:45.293 --> 09:46.168
this mustache would help
the overall look

09:46.252 --> 09:49.338
of Lola's whole--

09:49.422 --> 09:49.588
- He had to go.

09:51.632 --> 09:54.552
<i>[lively music]</i>

09:54.635 --> 09:56.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:56.596 --> 09:59.849
[Michael coughing]

09:59.932 --> 10:02.101
- Man, you sound awful.

10:03.394 --> 10:06.022
- Uh...what's wrong
with Michael?

10:06.105 --> 10:07.356
- We don't know.

10:07.440 --> 10:08.524
- Dude, you sure
you don't want to stay

10:08.607 --> 10:10.359
in your own bed
at our dorm?

10:10.443 --> 10:11.402
- Yeah.
I think I ought to hang here

10:11.485 --> 10:14.905
for a couple of days.
[coughs]

10:14.989 --> 10:16.699
- All right.
- Where's the nurse?

10:16.782 --> 10:17.825
- Shannon!

10:19.827 --> 10:21.037
- Oh.
[chuckles]

10:21.120 --> 10:22.788
When did she start working
at PCA?

10:22.872 --> 10:23.914
- About a month ago.

10:23.998 --> 10:25.458
Is one of you sick?

10:25.541 --> 10:26.667
- [coughing]

10:26.751 --> 10:28.377
- Yeah.
Michael here.

10:28.461 --> 10:29.920
- [groaning]

10:30.004 --> 10:31.881
I can barely stand up.

10:31.964 --> 10:33.966
Help me.

10:34.050 --> 10:36.761
- Oh, of course.

10:36.844 --> 10:38.387
- So soft.
[coughs]

10:38.471 --> 10:40.723
- Well, I 'd say
you're in good hands.

10:40.806 --> 10:42.725
- Very good hands.

10:42.808 --> 10:44.143
- [groans, coughs]

10:44.226 --> 10:45.311
- Well, feel better, man.

10:45.394 --> 10:46.562
- Oh, I'll try.

10:46.645 --> 10:48.647
[groaning]

10:48.731 --> 10:49.982
- Poor thing.

10:50.066 --> 10:51.609
- Oh...
thank you,

10:51.692 --> 10:54.445
but I'm just glad I have you
to take care of me.

10:54.528 --> 10:56.447
- Oh, I won't be
taking care of you.

10:56.530 --> 10:59.075
- Huh?
What do you mean?

10:59.158 --> 11:02.119
- Shannon's the nurse
for the lower school kids.

11:02.203 --> 11:03.913
[door opens]
- But I was told that--

11:03.996 --> 11:06.082
- Stupid Taco Hut!

11:06.165 --> 11:07.375
I asked for a macho beef
and bean burrito

11:07.458 --> 11:11.045
and they give me all beans!

11:11.128 --> 11:13.339
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

11:13.422 --> 11:14.715
What's wrong with this one?

11:14.799 --> 11:15.758
- He's very sick.

11:15.841 --> 11:17.093
- [laughs nervously]

11:17.176 --> 11:18.427
Actually, I feel much better.
Thank you--

11:18.511 --> 11:20.429
- Lay down.
- No, seriously, I--

11:20.513 --> 11:21.222
- Lay down!

11:21.305 --> 11:23.391
